members.intro: (현아) is a South Korean singer and rapper under . She was a member of the girl group , and its sub-group . On August 3, 2018, HyunA revealed that she has been dating , member of and , since May 2016. On November 28, 2019, HyunA posted a letter on Instagram opening up about her health. She revealed that, in 2016, she was diagnosed with depression and panic disorder and that she didn't believe it for a year. She revealed that she currently regularly gets treatment for it every two weeks. After experiencing fogginess of vision and collapsing, she thought it was a symptom of her panic disorder and ignored it. However, after seeing a university doctor, she received a brain wave test where she was diagnosed with vasovagal syncope. She ends the letter by thanking the people for reading her letter and stating that she will love and take care of herself. On January 27, 2019, she and her partner, , signed with 's new agency, . On October 18, PSY posted a photo of the couple on his Instagram account, saying that the singles of both were finished. On October 29, eleven teaser photos of " ", her first release under the new agency, were released.

Like and , she speaks English fluently. She graduated from Jamil Art High School on February 2, 2018. Before she joined Duble Kick company, she was a trainee at and had intentions of going on the survival reality show but she left before the show began. She also participated in the survival reality show but was eliminated. In March 2017, she joined and successfully debuted together with the additional member of the group's official return in April. Daisy is in-charge as the main rapper of the group and replaced in position. She was a former host of with her fellow member . On January 7, 2020, KBS broadcast an interview with Daisy on . She claimed that was rigged, stating the agency already planned to place her into the group despite being eliminated and that the chosen members had to pay for the production costs. She also explained that she has been in conflict with MLD after being prevented from promoting with the group since May 2019. When requesting to have her contract terminated, her agency demanded a 1.1 billion won penalty for breaking the contract. MLD Entertainment denied the claims stating that they were one-sided and have asked for an official apology from KBS. On February 14, 2019, it was reported that she and 's have been been dating for three months. Her agency, MLD Entertainment, and Song's agency, , issued conflicting statements, the former confirming the report while the latter denied it, explaining that they have met a few times but are not dating.

members.intro: (금주) is a singer, model, and actress under GG E&M Inc. She is a member of the pre-debut girl group . In April of 2016, Geumju appeared on the reality show alongside her twin sister . On the show, the twins talked about how they dreamed of becoming actresses even though their mother opposed the idea. The twins, who had been cast on the street and started acting out of curiosity about what it would be like, started making cameo appearances in several shows in the second grade of middle school. Their mother was worried the twins would not be eating well. Their father, however, was fully supportive of their girls' dream. He said all he wanted was his daughters to be happy. In 2018, the sisters were both trainees under Monstergram Inc. (now known as MARBLING E&M). Under this agency, Geumju became a part of the pre-debut four-member girl group Ping Pok. In January of 2019, the four-member girl group Ping Pok turned into the eight-member girl group . In February of 2019, Geumju and Jinju joined the trot survival show as a duo. They didn't make it past the audition. In April, they both joined GG E&M Inc. as trainees. On October 7, Geumju was announced as a new member of the upcoming girl group Roovylette after four of the previous members left the group. The group since rebranded as .

members.intro: She made solo debut on June 13, 2019 with the digital single " ". In May 2015, she participated in the reality survival show . She was eliminated in the final episode after achieving 9th place. In 2016, she participated in Mnet's survival television show, as a trainee representing . She finished the survival in first place, becoming the center of the girl group . On May 4, 2016, the group debuted with the mini album , and its title track, "Dream Girls". From October 2016 to April 2017, Somi along with 's were the hosts for the sixth season of the music show . After the disbandment of I.O.I on January 29, Somi signed an official artist contract with , meaning she would be able to pursue solo activities and brand endorsements until her official debut. Later, on February 10, she joined the second season of the variety show, , and debuted as a member of their special girl group in May 2017. Somi then went onto being cast in the reality-drama show, in May 2017, as a representative of I.O.I. She played the role of high school student named Bo-ram, and then later became part of a special girl group named formed by her fellow cast members in July 2017. On August 20, 2018, it was announced that Somi left , and confirmed to have joined 's sub-label on September 23, 2018 . In late November, it was reported that Somi was working on new music with the goal of making a solo debut in March 2019. It was later scheduled for May 1, then delayed to late May, and finally for June 13. Finally, on June 13, Somi debuted as a soloist with the digital single album " ". On music shows, she also performed the other track, "Outta My Head". On July 1, it was announced that I.O.I would make a return under a new agency called Studio Blue. The return would be in October 2019, later delayed to December, with nine members, sadly Somi not being one of them due to her solo activities. On February 7, 2020, she gratuated from Hanlim Arts School.

members.intro: (공민지), better known as , is a South Korean singer currently under . She was a member of the girl group and project group . She made her solo debut on April 17, 2017 with her first mini album . In 2009, Minzy, alongside then-labelmates , , and , debuted as members of 2NE1 with "Fire". Later that year, 2NE1 took a temporary hiatus as a group to release solo tracks, with Minzy and CL releasing "Please Don't Go" as a duo. On April 5, 2016, it was announced that Minzy decided to not renew her contract with YG Entertainment and officially left the group and the agency on May 5, 2016. In May 2016, Minzy signed with The Music Works and began preparation for a solo album. On January 17, 2017, Minzy was revealed as a cast member of the second season of . The show aired its first broadcast on February 10, where Minzy was appointed as the main singer, lead dancer and choreographer for the second generation of and was later voted in as the leader of the group in the third episode. The same month, Minzy released her first solo single "I Want To Love" as part of the soundtrack of the MBC drama . On April 3, Minzy announced that her debut solo mini-album will be released on April 17. The same day, she will hold her solo debut stage on . In September, she filed a request to terminate her contract with The Music Works and to be paid 50 million won in compensation. The injunction was denied later that year, as the court overseeing the lawsuit deemed the contract still valid.

members.name: Tzuyu
members.intro: (Korean: 쯔위; Japanese: ツウィ) is a Taiwanese singer under . She is the maknae of the girl group . On May 5, 2015, she became a contestant on JYP's newest survival show, . Unfortunately, in the final episode, she didn't made it to the final line-up. However, based on a unanimous decision, , along with the trainers and the A&R team, bought her back and included her in the group. They officially debuted on October 20, 2015 with their first mini album, Controversy arose as fans became skeptical of the motivations behind the decision of the addition of Tzuyu and previously eliminated . Tzuyu was a fan favorite throughout the series and JYP included her due to her popularity and star quality. The following day after the final episode, JYPE released a short statement about the addition of the two girls into the final lineup of the group: "We apologize for failing to clearly communicate the selection process, and we'd like to explain it in detail once again. The condition to be chosen as a final member was the votes made by the audience and viewers. However, leading up to the final episode, we thought that the seven members selected officially may leave something to be desired. So, in addition to the seven, we decided that one member would be added solely from viewer's opinions (Tzuyu) and one from solely 's opinion (Momo)." On November 28, 2015, Tzuyu, along with her non-Korean fellow members from appeared on the internet variety show . During the program, Tzuyu held up a Taiwanese flag to show her nationality. Member , , and did the same for their country, Japan. However, Tzuyu's action was picked up by the Taiwanese singer China-based , who opposes Taiwanese independence from China, and described Tzuyu on his Weibo account as a Taiwanese independence supporter. In response to the controversy, JYP China stated on it official Weibo account that, until the misunderstanding had been resolved, TWICE's activities in China would be halted. As an apology, a video of Tzuyu was released on JYPE's channel on January 15, 2016. In the video, she is seen standing in front of a gray wall, facing the camera in a casual attire. Speaking Chinese, she begins with a short self introduction, followed by "I'm sorry", and continous saying how proud she is about being Chinese. The video had a very polemical YouTube rating, alongside the general public stirring backlash against the video. Many political figures in Taiwan, including presidential candidates and the outgoing president, released statements supporting Tzuyu. Huang An was given backlash of his own, while JYP Entertainment's website suffered a DDoS attack. Both Huang An and JYP Entertainment were faced with subsequent legal threats over the flag incident.

On July 11, 2019, it was announced that Mina would stop participating in TWICE's world tour due to struggling with sudden extreme anxiety and insecurity towards performing on stage. On August 27, JYP Entertainment released a statement saying that after professional examinations, Mina was diagnosed with anxiety disorder. The main characteristics of symptoms are continuous anxiety or intermittent anxiety that occurs unexpectedly and also sudden changes in anxiety level. Based on this, her participation in the group's activities is being discussed with her and the members and has to be decided entirely based on Mina's objective state of health. On February 12, 2020, JYP commented on Mina's appearance at the concert in Fukuoka by saying that the condition of her health has stabilized. It was also stated that further activities will be carried out with consideration of her health.

members.name: Lee Jong Hyun
members.intro: (이종현) is a South Korean musician, singer-songwriter, and actor under . He is a former member of the group . Jonghyun was born on May 15, 1990, in Busan, South Korea. He was born into a middle-class family as the youngest of three kids. His family moved around constantly as a kid, eventually returning to Busan and settling there. Jonghyun regards Japan as his second home since he spent so much time there with his family. Jonghyun was always a fan of music and often listened to American rock music. He once saw Eric Clapton and decided that the life of a musician was the life he wanted to live. So, he enrolled in guitar classes and learned to play very quickly. During his middle school days, he also entered into martial arts but he knew music was his true passion. In 2007 Jonghyun auditioned for FNC Entertainment. He passed his audition and met some fellow musicians who would later be his band-mates. He then began his training at the FNC Academy. By 2009, CNBLUE had been formed and the group traveled to Japan to study music and see what kind of music audiences would like. The group would play live shows on the streets and they gained a good response from the Japanese public. This is when they began working on their debut album. In August of 2009, CNBLUE released their first mini album in Japan. It was an English language album and it was received well by the Japanese public. In January of 2010, they officially debuted in Korea with their first mini album with the title track "I'm a Loner". Jonghyun and one of his labelmates collaborated for the single " " in December of 2013. Later in 2010, Jonghyun and his bandmate, appeared in the film . Jonghyun was revered for his performance in the film and was thought he could do acting full-time. However, he did not want to put music aside, as that was his true passion. After that, he declined many opportunities to star in films, dramas, and variety shows. However, in 2012 the drama caught his attention and he became a part of the cast. Although he did well in the public's eye, he still felt reluctant and insecure. He has said that his strength is in his music, that he does well in music and lacks the confidence to do other things. His CEO even had to push him to audition for . From here on out, Jonghyun started to be in more and more casts. In 2013 and 2014 he starred in and respectively. His popularity was slowly increasing as CNBLUE continued to promote and he was cast in more and more dramas. In July 2016, Jonghyun debuted in Japan with his first solo album, and it was a hit in both Japan and South Korea. The album sold more than 13000 copies leading to Jonghyun having his first solo concert.

members.intro: On December 20, 2019, a teaser photo was released on the BTOB twitter teasing the single "3X2=6 Part 1". The single was to be a part of his single project where he was to release two songs every month for 3 months. The next day, teaser photos of him in the studio were released. On the 23rd, the track list was released with the audio teasers being released on the 24th. The single and the lyric video was officially released on the 26th and 27th respectively. A teaser photo displaying the date "4/6" was released on January 8, 2020 with another being released on the 10th. The track list for "3X2=6 Part 2" was revealed on the 13th with the audio teasers being released on the 15th. The single was released on the 16th with the lyric videos for the songs being released the next day. A teaser photo displaying "6/6" was released on February 1. The track list was released on the 4th with the audio teasers being released the next day. The single "3X2=6 Part 3" was released on the 6th with the lyric videos being released on the next day. On February 17, it was announced that he will be releasing the special album on March 2.

members.name: Leeteuk
members.intro: Leeteuk was born Park Jeongsu on July 1, 1983 as the youngest child in the family. Leeteuk's older sister, Park In-young, is an actress. When he was about 15 years old, Leeteuk's parents divorced. In 2000, Leeteuk was on vacation in Myeongdong with his sister and was spotted by a talent agent. He had a successful audition and signed on with the agency. That same year, he landed an extra role in the MBC drama , and later became a model for Pepsi for a brief period. Leeteuk was originally supposed to debut as a member of the group "Smile" with bandmate as a rival group to . After that plan fell through, Leeteuk and Donghae were both put in the rotational group . SUPER JUNIOR made their debut on November 6, 2005 with " ". In 2006 when SM began to recruit new members for the rotational group, the rotational system faced strong opposition and SM eventually dropped the idea after adding to the group. They then dropped the "'05" and officially became know as SUPER JUNIOR with Leeteuk as their leader. From 2006 to 2011, Leeteuk co-hosted " " with . He left the program to enlist in the military in 2011. He briefly returned in 2016 as a guest host. He also served as a host on and , and 's . He has also made numerous cameo appearances in dramas over the years, including , , and . On April 19, 2007, Leeteuk was on his way home after recording a program for . He was in SUPER JUNIOR's van with two of their managers, , Eunhyuk, and Kyuhyun. The driver of the vehicle was switching lanes on the highway when the left tire burst and the car slammed against the guard rail on the driver's side. The vehicle travelled about 30 meters before flipped over onto the right side. The seriousness of this accident caused injuries to each member, and hospitalized Leeteuk and Kyuhyun. Leeteuk received about 180 stitches in total while Kyuhyun was in a coma and had little chances of surviving. Luckily, they all survived and are promoting to this day. Later in Leeteuk's life, his father stayed with Leeteuk's grandparents, who suffered from dementia. His father was struggling to make ends meet and he developed severe depression. On January 2014, he suffocated Leeteuk's grandparents before hanging himself. His father left a note taking responsibilities for his actions and asking for forgiveness from his children.

members.name: Jonghyun
members.intro: (종현) was a South Korean singer and songwriter under SM Entertainment. He was a member of the boy group . He made his solo debut on January 12, 2015 with his first mini-album while his final album was released posthumously on January 23, 2018. On January 1, a mysterious video teaser of a triangle that expands into a square was released on the SMTOWN website. It was then confirmed that Jonghyun will make his solo debut with the mini album on January 12 with teaser photos and a teaser video being released on January 2. On January 3, it was announced that SMTOWN would be revealing a line up of artists that participated in the album, with being revealed on the same day. The next day, it was revealed that the singer-songwriter participated in the lyric making of the album. The title track of the mini album was announced to be "Crazy (Guilty Pleasure)", which features the rapper Iron, on January 5 through a teaser video. The song was described to be a medium tempo retro pop song influenced by neo soul and funk genres. On January 6, it was announced that Jonghyun would be pre-releasing the song "Déjà-Boo", featuring , on January 7. The track list for the mini album was revealed the next day and featured a total of 7 songs, including the bonus track, along with the symbols "+???" indicating an additional song. On the same day, the song "Déjà-Boo" was pre-released and took charge of the top spot on real time charts. A highlight medley for the mini album was released on January 8 with the music video for "Crazy (Guilty Pleasure)" dropping the next day. A performance video for "Déjà-Boo" was released on January 10, two days after his showcase stage. The mini album was officially released on January 12 and swept number one on different music charts. On January 14, a dance practice video for the song "Hallelujah" was released.

members.name: CNU
members.intro: (신우) is a South Korean singer-songwriter, rapper, and actor under . He is a member of the boy group . CNU was born on June 16, 1991. He has one older sister who is 5 years older than him, making his family 4 members. CNU says that he resembles his mother more. CNU's dream as a child was to be a singer. His mother was a trot singer and his sister did pansori. He learned to play the piano at 3 years old and then decided to learn guitar too. In his school days, he joined a rock band with one of his friends, which led him to discovering his true passion for music. He would often visit Seoul and audition to be a singer with his friends. However, he was always the only one that got the unsatisfactory result. His older sister encouraged him to continue to practice and become even better so he would eventually get a good result. CNU debuted as a member of B1A4 on April 11, 2011 on MBC's . He was the last member to join B1A4. He has said that when he first debuted he felt really awkward and didn't feel like himself. But as time has passed, he feels he has gotten more natural and comfortable with the attention and he doesn't try to hide himself as much anymore. Since then, CNU has been an active member of B1A4. He has also developed a career in the musical theater world as he has been in a couple of shows throughout the years ​​ ​​​​​

members.name: Jinyoung (B1A4)
members.intro: (진영) is a South Korean singer-songwriter, producer, and actor. He was a member of the boy group . Jinyoung was born November 18, 1991 rounding his family up to 4. He has one older sister who is 2 years older than him. He's always had a love for singing and once, when is family was on vacation, they put their hotel room arrangements on the line so he could sing in a talent show. He was scouted by when he was in middle school after they found a picture of him on the Korean social media site 'Cyworld'. Jinyoung was the first member of the new boy group B1A4 to be revealed to the public. Once all the members were revealed, B1A4 officially debuted on April 21, 2011 on MBC's . Jinyoung did not start composing by learning professionally. He simply was messing around with different programs until he slowly got better at it. When B1A4 made a comeback with their song , a song that Jinyoung composed, he started gaining attention for more than his singing. High level professionals in the industry praised him highly for the work he had created. From here he started to compose more songs for B1A4 and other artist and projects. He also began to produce some songs for special projects such as and . Jinyoung also began to dabble in the acting field, starring in a number of rolls on the big screen and in day-time dramas.

On August 15, 2016, Alex announced that she became the group's new leader. On February 21, 2017, DR Music was approached by a production company with an acting opportunity for Alex. On August 12, 2017, RaNia released their fifth mini-album , the promotion for the album became controversial after fans noticed that Alex has little to no lines, and that she spent the majority of performances standing off to the side while the other girls danced and sang. Following her departure, Alex took to Twitter and criticized the company in regards to how she was treated and her departure, saying "People think they can push you around, take advantage of you, manipulate you, violate you then throw you in the trash and walk. members.intro: (허찬미; also known simply as ) is a South Korean singer currently under Mostable Music. She is best known for being a former member of the co-ed group , the girl group and as a contestant in and later . Chanmi started in her career in 2004 where she signed with S.M. Entertainment as a trainee. She trained for a long time until she didn't make the final cut to be part of Girls' Generation due to the fact she was the youngest and was only in seventh grade. In October 2010, Chanmi debuted with under Core Contents Media. By 2013, Co-ed School was no longer active, allowing Chanmi to leave the group. In 2011, Chanmi debuted with a subgroup of Co-ed School, . Chanmi left F-ve dolls in 2012 to pursue her solo career that never came to fruition. She left Core Contents Media the same year. Chanmi then signed with as a trainee, but it was later revealed she was under . Duble Kick Entertainment reported that she would not participate in their own reality survival show, , instead, the company stated that they had plans for her to debut in another group. In 2017, Chanmi joined as a trainee under Mostable Music. She made it to the third round of eliminations and was eliminated. Her final rank was #20. In MIXNINE, it was revealed that she along with three other girls were preparing to debut under the agency's new girl group , however as of now, the debut has been cancelled for unknown reasons.

members.name: Sulli
members.intro: (설리) was a South Korean singer-songwriter, actress and model under . She was a member of the girl group , but left the group on August 2015 to focus on her acting career. In June 2019, it was announced that Sulli was set to make a return to the idol scene. She debuted as a soloist on June 29, 2019 with the digital single album " ". On October 14, 2019, Sulli passed away at her home in Seongnam, Gyeonggi-do in a suspected suicide. Sulli was born March 29, 1994, in Busan, South Korea. In 2005, Sulli joined and debuted as a child actress at age 11 in the SBS drama . She had various roles in multiple films over the next four years until her idol debut on September 5, 2009 in the girl group with the digital single " ". Following her debut as an idol, Sulli returned as an actress and starred in as lead in in 2012. In 2013, Sulli became the face of makeup brand Etude House along with fellow f(x) member . In 2014, Sulli appeared in hit films, and . During promotions for , Sulli took a break from all activities due to being mentally and physically exhausted from the continuous, malicious comments and false rumors that had been spread about her. SM Entertainment later announced to take legal action against the individual spreading malicious rumors. Two months later, SM announced the person behind the rumors was caught and filed a suit against them on charges of defamation. However, charges against the accused were dropped by SM and Sulli after the accused apologized. On August 7, 2015, SM announced that Sulli had left f(x) to focus on her acting career. On November 9, 2018, Sulli was a featured singer in 's single " ". Sulli later made her return to music on June 29, 2019 to debut as a soloist with the digital single album " ". The same day, a special stage titled was held in SM Town Theatre. On October 14, 2019, Sulli was found dead at her home in Seongnam, Gyeonggi-do by her manager who was unable to reach her the day before. It was later confirmed by the police with the cause of death under investigation under the assumption that she took her own life. Sulli first attended Jungbu Elementary School in Busan and later transferred to Seoul Cheongdam Elementary School. After completing her primary education, she attended Chungdam Middle School and later graduated from the Department of Theatre & Film in the . In August 2014, media outlet Dispatch published a series of photos that appears to revealed Sulli out on an evening date with 's . Dispatch reported that an acquaintance of both said the two were in ambiguous state of their relationship when they were first captured together in August of last year. Since then, their relationship continued to progress. Soon after the publication of the "date" photos, SM Entertainment along with confirmed that the two were in a relationship. In March 2017, according to Star News, Sulli and Choiza were reported to have broken up after two years and seven months since they were first revealed to be dating. Their breakup was confirmed by both of their agencies with Amoeba Culture stating: "Because it's our artist's personal life, we want to be cautious, but due to a lot of interest and concern, we're releasing a statement. Choiza and Sulli, due to their busy schedules and different ways of life, naturally grew apart. The time they spent together will remain as a good memory, and they will be moving forward as friends and colleagues." A few months later after her breakup with Choiza, Sulli and band director Kim Min-joon were confirmed by Dispatch to be in a relationship after dating for two months in May, beginning their relationship in March. Two months later in July, Kim Min-joon announced their breakup on his private social media channel, writing to his fans: "Since the beginning of our relationship was revealed to everyone in a situation without our say, I am writing this because I think I should also reveal the end. Choi Jin-ri and I have decided to go our separate ways."

members.name: Hyelin
members.intro: (혜린) is a South Korean singer. She is a member of the girl group . Alongside , she joined in April, 2012. Hyelin had wanted to be a singer from a young age, she was so passionate about this dream that once when her father implied she couldn't do it, she didn't speak to him for months after. She joined in 2011 but failed to advance. After audition and training with EXID's original company, she was going to be a member of the original lineup of EXID but was cut from the lineup before debut. However after three members left, she was added to the lineup (for her vocals and dancing) alongside former vocal coach to create the five-member group known since then. In 2016, EXID promoted their first full album . It was on this album that the long awaited duo of Hyelin and Jeonghwa would come with the song "Are You Hungry?". Other than this bright and quirky track, Hyelin only participated in group tracks for this album. Due to Solji's thyroid condition, Hyelin had to take over main vocalist responsibilities in EXID's songs and performances. Because she was the only member with enough skill in her upper range to stand in for Solji, she had to sing Solji's parts in their older songs. She also had to take over all adlibs of new songs. EXID's first promotions without Solji began with the title track "Night Rather Than Day" from their third mini album where the music is more chill and less exciting than their normal music. EXID came back with "DDD" and the mini album in November of the same year and with that album came a solo track for Hyelin which she participated in writing for. The solo track was called "Foolish" and was Hyelin's first solo work since joining EXID. EXID first promoted in 2018 in April with the single album " ". This song and it's promotions caused Hyelin's popularity to rise more than ever before as she sings the highest note to be in an EXID song on it, and because of her newly long and straight black hair. Her dance skills were also shown off much more in this comeback than previous comebacks, as legs and footwork were more emphasized and this is something Hyelin is much more comfortable with and good at than their normal sexy style of dancing that emphasizes their hips. On December 20, 2016, Banana Culture announced that Solji had been diagnosed with hyperthyroidism, and would take a break on the group's activities to focus on her recovery. The group would continue the activities with 4-members. In January 2018, she underwent orbital decompression surgery. Her first apperance to the publick was through the reality show , and her first comeback with EXID was in the digital single " ", release in November that year. On February 4, several media outlets reported that the singer had decided to terminate her contract with . Later that day, the reports were confirmed by Solji, however, a source at Banana Culture commented that the termination was still being discussed. On March 23, announced that the singer had recently signed a contract with them, confirming her departure from Banana and the change of agencies.

In response, his agency confirmed and completed that they progressed their relationship while filming for tvN's upcoming drama "Studio Vibes". On June 6, Jang Jae Jin accused him on cheating on her by uploading a series of posts on Instagram. On the following day, Tae Hyun responded to the accusations. He released a statement saying that at the moment, he is sorting things out and will issue an apology and an explanation as soon as possible. In 2011, Tae Hyun was recruited as a trainee at YG Entertainment through an audition. He performed as a backup dancer at the 2011 YG Family Concert. In 2013, he competed in the reality program as a trainee in "Team A", which went on to debut as WINNER. He co-composed and co-wrote two of the songs used in the competition. The same year, he appeared in then-label-mate 's music video for "Ringa Linga". In December, he and the rest of WINNER appeared in their own variety program, , which aired on Mnet.

On March 13, 2020, it was announced Hyelim has been dating a non-celebrity for seven years. The couple will be part of MBC's upcoming variety show . members.intro: (라이관린; or ) is a Taiwanese rapper under . He is best known for finishing 7th in making him a member of the project group . He is also a member of the unit with 's . In 2017, he was a contestant on Mnet's survival show . He finished in 7th place thus making him a member of the project group . The group debuted on August 7, 2017 with their first mini album and concluded activities following their final concert on January 27, 2019. Following Wanna One's disbandment, Kuanlin became a member of the unit duo , alongside 's . They debuted on March 11 with the release of their first mini album . On July 20, he requested to terminate his contract with Cube Entertainment , the reason being Cube violated the norms of the contract, and he had his management rights sold to a third-party company. However, Cube affirmed that there was no legal cause to terminate the contract , and that they would plan to respond actively to the allegation by legal means. On August 7, 2019, the first questioning between Kuanlin's representatives and Cube started on the Seoul Central District Court. On November 21, 2019, Kuanlin's request was dismissed by the court, with Cube stating there was no reason behind the termination request, despite Kuanlin's side proving otherwise. This in turn caused an outrage on behalf of Kuanlin's fans on social media, using the hashtag #StandByKuanlin , demanding the liberation of Kuanlin from the company.
